         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/10/89. ¶  ¶ The Menkea, dear Prof. Tate, I have carefully compared, and find it absolutely identical with M. sphaerocarpa. The discrepancies from the descriptions simply arise from the plant, got a...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.10.18</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Ralph Tate</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Barr Smith Library, University of Adelaide, SA.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/10/89.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Menkea, dear Prof. Tate, I have carefully compared, and find it absolutely identical with M. sphaerocarpa. The discrepancies from the descriptions simply arise from the plant, got a Mt Olga,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NT.</p>
               </note> being more advanced towards ripening its fruits, when the style somewhat elongates.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Hakea is = H. purpurea Hooker var. simplicifolia.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No publication of the variety name has been found; it is not used in Tate (1890), where </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">H. purpurea</seg>
                     <seg style=""> is listed in 'Additions and corrections', p. 302.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> While in H. lorea the simple-leaved form is the prevailing, in H. purpurea the one with dichotomously divided leaves is the more frequent form.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nothing can be done with the flowerless and fruitless Eucalyptus. It may be, as sent, only the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">young</hi>
               </seg> state of a narrow-leaved species. It is not E. pulverulenta</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20pulverulenta">Eucalyptus pulverulenta</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hakea%20lorea">Hakea lorea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">Hakea purpurea <seg style="font-style: normal; ">var</seg> simplicifolia</p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Menkea%20sphaerocarpa">Menkea sphaerocarpa</name>
            </p>
         </div>
